article.headline: Colorado 74, Southern Cal 50
article.story: LOS ANGELES -- Andre Roberson had 13 points and 10 rebounds as Colorado beat Southern California 74-50 on Thursday night, sending the Trojans to their ninth straight loss. Carlon Brown scored 13 points with nine rebounds for the Buffaloes (14-6, 6-2), who used a 23-4 run spanning both halves in winning their first Pac-12 road game. Askia Booker scored 13, Austin Dufault 11 and Jeremy Adams 10. Maurice Jones scored 13 points to lead the Trojans (5-16, 0-8), who shot 32 percent overall and went 5 of 25 on 3-pointers. Roberson hit a layup and a free throw coming out of halftime to make the lead 40-26. After USC's James Blascyk scored on a jumper with 17:33 left, the Trojans went scoreless for nearly 6 minutes.
